%% CURRENT auth flow — matches CLAUDE.md "Auth chain" + TRD §3.5.
%% No backend API hop (see System Architecture LR.mmd). Role/tenant resolver
%% is TES-34, in progress: today the dashboard falls back to '?role=' preview
%% override rather than the Memberships/Resolve steps below.
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant Browser as Browser
  participant Proxy as proxy.ts (Clerk middleware)
  participant Next as Server Component / Route Handler
  participant Clerk as Clerk
  participant Supa as createSupabaseServerClient()
  participant DB as Supabase Postgres (RLS)

  Browser->>Proxy: Open protected route
  Proxy->>Clerk: Verify session
  alt No session
    Clerk-->>Proxy: Unauthenticated
    Proxy-->>Browser: Redirect to /sign-in
  else Session valid
    Clerk-->>Proxy: User identity
    Proxy->>Next: Continue request
    Next->>Clerk: getToken({ template: 'supabase' })
    Clerk-->>Next: Clerk JWT
    Next->>Supa: Attach JWT as bearer (anon key client)
    Supa->>DB: current_profile_id() via app_private.current_clerk_user_id()
    DB-->>Supa: profile_id, role
    Note over Next,DB: Gap TES-34 - resolver not yet wired into pages, falls back to a role query-param preview override
    Supa->>DB: profile_tenant_memberships (resolve default tenant)
    DB-->>Supa: tenant_id(s), is_default
    Next->>DB: Tenant-scoped query (RLS-enforced)
    alt RLS allows
      DB-->>Next: Scoped rows only
      opt File operation
        Next->>DB: Signed URL / storage read (tenant-UUID path prefix)
      end
      Next-->>Browser: Render UI
    else RLS denies
      DB-->>Next: Zero rows / policy violation
      Next-->>Browser: 403 / access-denied state
    end
  end
